//////////
package.json
> entry point to application
> containes all the packages
> script (start,build,test)
> metadata(name,version,description)

//////////
Step to generate package.json
**NodeJS must be install in system
> go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm init
> answer all questions
> type "yes"

//////////
Step to install package.
> go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm i packagename/npm i packagename@3.2.9

//////////
Step to generate react application
> go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> npx create-react-app appname

#window
// One Time
> open cmd as administrator
> npm i -g create-react-app

// next all time you need new app
> go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> create-react-app appname

//mac/linux
// One Time
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g create-react-app

// next all time you need new app
> go inside the folder using terminal
> create-react-app appname

//////////
Step to run react application
> go inside the react app folder using cmd/terminal
> npm start

